<img src="https://biz-file.com/c/1906/502837-625x325.jpg?2" alt="FCJ Excellence Awards: 2019 finalists announced!" width="625" height="325">© 123RF.com.These journalists and newspapers will be recognised for work published during 2018. Finalists will shortly receive an invitation to the awards gala dinner to be held at Leriba Hotel and Spa in Centurion on 19 July 2019.The competition was judged by seasoned veterans of the newspaper and community news industry. The writing, newspaper of the year and front page of the year categories were judged by Dr Thalyta Swanepoel, (convener of judges from the North-West University), Cornia Pretorius (NWU), Joe Thloloe (former press ombudsman), Virginia Keppler (Vrye Weekblad, former bureau chief: The Citizen), André Gouws (NWU online lecturer and former Beeld reporter) and Tarina Coetzee (former chief sub-editor at the Citizen and typography editor at Media24).All photography categories were judged by Roger Sedres, Leon Muller and Sharief Jaffer.The finalists are:PhotographyGeneral Michelle Pienaar, George HeraldRonald Sibiya, Pretoria Rekord Taylor Meyer, Village NewsZita Goldswain, Witbank NewsNews Bianca du Plessis, Hermanus TimesCarina Roux, TygerburgerJP Myburg, KlerksdorpSan Marie Cronje, Ridge Times Sport Blake Linder, Knysna Plett HeraldCarina Roux, TygerburgerElsje Vermeulen, VaalweekbladEttienne van Rensburg, VaalweekbladHugo Redelinghuys, George Herald Photographer of the Year Carina Roux, Tygerburger Elsje Vermeulen, VaalweekbladSalome Kotze, Klerksdorp RekordWritingDigital reporting Kristy Kolberg, George Herald Sibonele Mtshali, Southern Courier Headlines Bertus de Bruyn, Letaba Herald Dalene Naude, Middelburg ObserverDanie Jacobs, Klerksdorp Record Hannes Visser, Oudtshoorn CourantKristy Kolberg, George HeraldMariette Strydom, Boland MediaMurray Stewart, The Village NewsPieter Delport, Bloemfontein CourantWouter Pienaar, Potchefstroom HeraldZita Goldswain, Witbank NewsEditorial Comment Daleen Fouche, Hermanus Time